e<br>&gt;<br>&gt; * Everyone but me has been traveling so getting things together has been a<br>&gt; little hard.<br>&gt;<br>&gt; * I have been on Nate&#39;s case a lot about what collections, strides, sequences,<br>&gt; etc mean and should be named.<br></p><p>Thanks for the update.  FWIW I don&#39;t expect anything of anyone; I just<br>wanted to let everybody involved know that it could still get fixed for<br>Swift 3 but we&#39;ll need to move fast.<br></p><p>Cheers,<br></p><p>-- <br>Dave<br></p></div><ul class="comments"><li class="comment"><div class="avatar"><img src="https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/60dcb74d816e29b2aa6b9c0b5969670e?s=50"></div><header><strong>[Draft]: Introducing a striding(by:) method on 3.0 ranges</strong> from <string>Xiaodi Wu</string> &lt;xiaodi.wu at gmail.com&gt;<p>April 26, 2016 at 04:00:00pm</p></header><div class="content"><p>On Tue, Apr 26, 2016 at 4:08 PM, Dave Abrahams via swift-evolution &lt;<br>swift-evolution at swift.org&gt; wrote:<br></p><p>&gt;<br>&gt; on Mon Apr 25 2016, Erica Sadun &lt;swift-evolution at swift.org&gt; wrote:<br>&gt;<br>&gt; &gt; On Apr 25, 2016, at 7:15 PM, Xiaodi Wu via swift-evolution<br>&gt; &gt; &lt;swift-evolution at swift.org&gt; wrote:<br>&gt; &gt;<br>&gt; &gt;     Yup, we&#39;re going to try to touch base, the authors of the current<br>&gt; draft that<br>&gt; &gt;     is, sometime this week. More to come, hopefully.<br>&gt; &gt;<br>&gt; &gt;     On Mon, Apr 25, 2016 at 8:13 PM, Dave Abrahams via swift-evolution<br>&gt; &gt;     &lt;swift-evolution at swift.org&gt; wrote:<br>&gt; &gt;<br>&gt; &gt;         After some reflection, I don&#39;t really want to see a construct<br>&gt; like #3 in<br>&gt; &gt;         the standard library, and Chris has clarified for me that the<br>&gt; standard<br>&gt; &gt;         library doesn&#39;t need to solve the migration problems created by<br>&gt; the<br>&gt; &gt;         removal of C-style “for” loops. So, if I have inadvertently<br>&gt; killed<br>&gt; &gt;         